        <h3> SUMMARY </h3> <hr> 
        Computer Science STudent. I am motivated and passionate by IT and sustainable development. I have been a scout member since I was 5. I have 19 years of experience helping people in different ways. Not only that, but I spent seven years of experience in the Red Cross to help people like to find shelter, food, and other basic needs for humans. I am open-minded and a great team player. I am a stern believer that Curiosity and Perseverance matter for any problem-solving. Passionate computer engineer with a passion for hardware development, societal evaluation of computer-related impacts, and developing computer applications to assist businesses and organizations in achieving their goals for African development. Currently, a first-year computer science student pursuing an honors science degree.

